main event: A report was filed regarding a sighting of a ring of lights with a dark center in the sky on July 29, 1958, in the Bronx, New York.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 5 minutes,The object ascended and diminished in size while moving in and out of the clouds,The report concluded there was insufficient data for evaluation,There were no confirmed weather reports corroborating the visibility of the object,The report could not determine if the object was caused by known aerial phenomena.
sighted object: ring of lights with dark center
witness description: No specific witnesses were mentioned, but the report notes that lawyers observed the object overhead.
